verbose_text: Independently of the concentration used, TW2 (CMC; 0.0074% w/v) was able to inhibit the binding of FITC-LPS to hCAS, while, as expected, concentrations of about 0.0125% (above the CMC) were required to completely inhibit the binding of FITC-LPS to empty wells (XREF_FIG).
